s roosted in a variety of tree species and manmade structures in natural and developed areas. Half of the bats departed across Lake Erie (minimum crossing distance\n              c.\n              38\u2003km) while half departed along the shoreline.\n            \n            \n              4.\n              \u2002Simulations predicted a migration rate of\n              c.\n              250\u2013275\u2003km per day and suggest that all but one of the bats in our study carried sufficient fuel stores to reach the putative wintering area (estimated distance 1500\u2003km) without further refuelling.\n            \n            \n              5.\n              \u2002Our results suggest that migrating bats stopover for sanctuary or short\u2010term rest as opposed to extended rest and refuelling as in many songbirds. Daily torpor could reduce energy costs when not in flight, minimizing the need for extended stopovers and allowing bats to potentially complete their migration at a fraction of the time and energy cost of similar sized birds.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "McGuire, Liam P.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Guglielmo, Christopher G.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Mackenzie, Stuart A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Taylor, Philip D.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/3c5bdd016176466b53fbae0ec34bc2c9", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/6278862e5def717f8dc916fed88ecae4e040249e060608c9ba5e211d755273a8", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/6IYZ6DNS", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/6IYZ6DNS", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/523749113d9a51f4fed371ca25161f3b!/b323752-326